            <biogHist>
                <p>James Carmichael Watson was the son of William John Watson, succeeding him in the
                    chair of Celtic at the University of Edinburgh in 1938. Before his early death
                    in the Second World War, he edited volumes 4 and 5 of his grandfather Alexander
                    Carmichael's <span localType="mods-titleinfo">Carmina Gadelica</span>. Serving
                    as an ordinary seaman during the war, he died when his ship HMS Jaguar was
                    torpedoed and sunk off the Egyptian coast.</p>
